Copyright.AdditionalInfo: British Columbia Array 2009 (BC) UofA project name - BCA Data collected By Edward Bertrand, Greg Nieuwenhuis, Dennis Rippe, Arthur Schilling Data was collected between June 5, 2009 and July 13, 2009 Funding provided through: (1) Natural Resources Canada GEMS Project - Geomapping for Energy and Minerals (2) NSERC Discovery Grant to Martyn Unsworth This folder contains two subfolders: 1) edi - the processed edi files containing the impedance data calculated from the time series (can be read by most standard MT software) 2) raw - this folder contains the raw time series data (.raw), each station is subdivided into its own folder - each station folder contains a .hdr file with pertinent information and comments for processing - some stations also have a .gps file within their folder, meaning that station could not get a gps lock, and the .gps file contains the station coordinates, as well as start and times of the time series. The electrodes at some of the stations have been rotated (.hdr files describe the rotation, if any. counterclockwise rotations mean the north electrode was moved to the west, and the east electrode has been moved to the north) .gps files contain the time series start time (year month day hour minute second), then latitude and longitude, and finally magnetic declination Greg Nieuwenhuis, Jan. 2011
